Position Description
Senior Business Development ManagerThis is an individual contributor role responsible for growing the Egencia business across Asia. The successful candidate will be responsible for developing and managing a sales strategy and pipeline, coordinating multi-market travel tenders, presenting the Egencia value proposition to perspective clients, working with our Egencia sales teams around the world and with our APAC Egencia Global Affiliate partners in growing our customer base.Responsibilities:- define and lead the execution of the business development strategy Egencia's proprietary and EGA business.- coordinate the Asian market responses multi-market travel agency tenders originating outside of Asia- develop and manage a pipeline of Asia-based business prospects, from qualification to signature- meet or exceed an annual sales target for new Asia-based business- work closely with Marketing and Product Development in developing and implementing an Asia- focused value proposition- present the Egencia value proposition and develop customer-focused travel management solutions for prospective clients- work closely with and influences the areas of sales, implementation, and account management colleagues around the world- strengthen our relationships with Egencia Global Affiliate agencies across Asia by demonstrating on-going value creation- inspire Egencia sales professionals around the world to sell Egencia in APAC- respond to RFP's- present to perspective clientsQualifications:- ability to work independently, self motivate and take initiative- ability to solve complex problems- ability to deal effectively with ambiguity- ability to work effectively across diverse cultures- ability to listen, probe, and develop appropriate customer solutions- ability to partner with CFO level management- personal resilience and accountability- drive for results- a strong will to winWork Experience and Education Guidelines:- proven experience in sales and/or account management- proven ability to manage a sales pipeline and deliver expected results- proven ability to build and leverage relationships- proven ability to develop an effective personal network within a matrix organisation- knowledge of Egencia products and benefits is a plus- experience within Egencia or other global TMC is a plus, but not essential- experience working in Mandarin is a plus, but not essentialCore Competencies:- consultative selling- fluency in spoken and written English- sales pipeline management- building and leverage relationships- cross-functional collaboration- driving results- knowledge of travel management concepts and practices- knowledge of corporate travel technology- fluency in Mandarin is a plus, but not essential About Expedia, Inc.Our mission is to revolutionize travel through the power of technology.Collectively, the Expedia, Inc. brands cover virtually every aspect of researching, planning, and booking travel, from choosing the best airplane seat, to reading personal travel reviews of hotels, to planning what to do in a destination once you arrive. The Expedia, Inc. portfolio serves both leisure and business travellers with tastes and budgets ranging from modest to luxury. Expedia delivers consumer travel demand from nearly every continent to nearly 149,000 hotels and hundreds of airlines, tour operators, car rental companies and destination services supply partners. Please visit company website to learn more about our travel brands.This employer participates in E-Verify. The employer will provide the Social Security Administration (SSA) and, if necessary, the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) with information from each new employee's I-9 to confirm work authorization.*LI-LC1
